#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn3.10"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn3.10:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.10:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga "
msgstr "1. Shackles "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn3.10:0.3"
msgid "10. Bandhanasutta "
msgstr "10. Shackles "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn3.10:1.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena raññā pasenadinā kosalena mahājanakāyo bandhāpito hoti, appekacce rajjūhi appekacce andūhi appekacce saṅkhalikāhi. "
msgstr "Now at that time a large group of people had been put in shackles by King Pasenadi of Kosala—some in ropes, some in manacles, some in chains. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.77, pts2ed1.175, sc2
msgctxt "sn3.10:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pavisiṃsu. "
msgstr "Then several mendicants robed up in the morning and, taking their bowls and robes, entered Sāvatthī for alms. "

msgctxt "sn3.10:2.2"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkantā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then, after the meal, when they returned from alms-round, they went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what was happening. "

msgctxt "sn3.10:2.3"
msgid "“idha, bhante, raññā pasenadinā kosalena mahājanakāyo bandhāpito, appekacce rajjūhi appekacce andūhi appekacce saṅkhalikāhī”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn3.10:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etamatthaṃ viditvā tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imā gāthāyo abhāsi: "
msgstr "Then, knowing the meaning of this, on that occasion the Buddha recited these verses: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn3.10:4.1"
msgid "“Na taṃ daḷhaṃ bandhanamāhu dhīrā, "
msgstr "“The wise say that shackle is not strong "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.10:4.2"
msgid "Yadāyasaṃ dārujaṃ pabbajañca; "
msgstr "that’s made of iron, wood, or knots. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.10:4.3"
msgid "Sārattarattā maṇikuṇḍalesu, "
msgstr "But obsession with jewels and earrings, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.10:4.4"
msgid "Puttesu dāresu ca yā apekkhā. "
msgstr "concern for your partners and children: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.176, sc5
msgctxt "sn3.10:5.1"
msgid "Etaṃ daḷhaṃ bandhanamāhu dhīrā, "
msgstr "this the wise say is a strong shackle "

# NOTE: I assume asithila, with a elided metri causa. BB’s “supple” notwithstanding, sithila yields exactly the wrong meaning.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.10:5.2"
msgid "Ohārinaṃ sithilaṃ duppamuñcaṃ; "
msgstr "that drags you down, tight, hard to escape. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.10:5.3"
msgid "Etampi chetvāna paribbajanti, "
msgstr "They cut this too and go forth, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.10:5.4"
msgid "Anapekkhino kāmasukhaṃ pahāyā”ti. "
msgstr "unconcerned, having given up sensual pleasures.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn3.10:5.5"
msgid "Paṭhamo vaggo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn3.10:6.1"
msgid "Daharo puriso jarā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.10:6.2"
msgid "piyaṃ attānarakkhito; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.10:6.3"
msgid "Appakā aḍḍakaraṇaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.10:6.4"
msgid "mallikā yaññabandhananti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
